I love Sir John; he's a fantastic makeup artist, but that's not a credible test. And can we talk about hygiene and sanitation???

First of all - NEVER blow on makeup products or brushes. HYGIENE PLEASE!

Second, I've used plenty of loose powder formulas that were lighter than air - but still gathered, creased, and accentuated fine lines.

Finally, It's all about the micron size of the powder particles, the type of anti-caking additives in the formula, and any "skincare benefit" ingredients added for marketing purposes. THAT is what determines the performance of a loose powder.

Source: @glamwithsuzan
